Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.41,0:01:49.06,Title,,0,0,0,,The Forgotten Cell Phone\N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.03,0:01:52.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.52,0:01:54.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.90,0:01:56.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.10,0:01:56.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.99,0:01:58.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.08,0:01:59.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.45,0:02:00.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.74,0:02:05.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the day before yesterday to yesterday, there were three calls in total.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.29,0:02:06.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three calls?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.79,0:02:08.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did they say?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.79,0:02:13.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first person was on his way to a job interview, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.75,0:02:16.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He left the paper with the address at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.84,0:02:21.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wanted to get the address by any means necessary...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.09,0:02:23.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he probably wouldn't get the job if the interviewer found this out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.26,0:02:28.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The second person got a phone call from their daughter, who had run away from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.10,0:02:33.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They wanted to know where the call had been made from.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.19,0:02:38.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The third person said he met a friendly person while traveling...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.65,0:02:42.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who accidentally left his cell phone in the caller's bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.07,0:02:48.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wanted to know this person's name and address so he could return it to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.33,0:02:50.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the one!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.62,0:02:52.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the only one where a cell phone is mentioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.21,0:02:54.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.50,0:02:58.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And also, that last person is the only one who also wanted to get the person's home phone number.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.88,0:03:00.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, what was the number?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.17,0:03:05.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They refused to help him, so there wasn't any record.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.56,0:03:09.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, none of those three made the calls from their houses.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.43,0:03:12.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They made them outside, so we have no way to tell who or where they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.94,0:03:13.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.15,0:03:18.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One person called from a train platform at Beika Station in the evening two nights ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.86,0:03:22.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One person called from a sports shop called "Apollo" yesterday at noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.03,0:03:25.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other person called from a restaurant named "Columbo" last evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.12,0:03:34.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, they forgot which of these was which, so we don't know when or where the one we need was.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.42,0:03:37.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.09,0:03:42.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They also said the person who asked for the phone number suddenly hung up on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.34,0:03:44.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suddenly?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.31,0:03:48.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there was some noise over the phone at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.72,0:03:50.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A noise that almost blocked out the conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.72,0:03:51.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A really loud noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.89,0:03:58.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it was only for a short moment so they couldn't really discern what kind of noise it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.53,0:04:03.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like we have no choice but to call those places and ask...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.49,0:04:06.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll have to get in contact with the places those three people called from.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.66,0:04:09.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I passed the exams!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.83,0:04:11.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's great!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.79,0:04:12.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was all thanks to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.95,0:04:14.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now we can all relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.66,0:04:15.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here's your change.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.88,0:04:19.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here goes the first call.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.50,0:04:20.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.84,0:04:30.55,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\an8\be10}The Tohto Loop Line train will be arriving shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.22,0:04:27.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The public phone on the platform?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.35,0:04:31.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want to ask about the night before yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.01,0:04:33.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were many people using the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.73,0:04:37.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, guess it can't be helped...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.02,0:04:40.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, could it be that person?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.27,0:04:45.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person who was hesitating about whether or not to make a phone call.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.45,0:04:48.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, there was a person like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.07,0:04:53.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was wearing a long coat and had a face like that of a dangerous person.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.54,0:04:55.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's been coming to the station quite frequently lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.28,0:05:00.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When that person was on the phone, was there a loud noise nearby?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.38,0:05:01.42,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A loud noise?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.42,0:05:02.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.46,0:05:04.53,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That happens all the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.76,0:05:07.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a train station after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.09,0:05:08.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.01,0:05:12.64,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\an8\be10}The train headed toward Kenbashi will arrive at Platform Number 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.64,0:05:15.10,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\an8\be10}Boarding passengers should stand behind the white line.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.97,0:05:15.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.10,0:05:16.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The announcements at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.69,0:05:18.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.73,0:05:20.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seems like it's hard to communicate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.88,0:05:21.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.15,0:05:22.53,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.86,0:05:24.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you heard that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.90,0:05:26.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the loud noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.91,0:05:27.70,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.70,0:05:29.07,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We understand now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.31,0:05:29.70,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Besides that, do you have any other clues about the dangerous man wearing a long coat?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.70,0:05:33.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides that, do you have any other clues about the dangerous man wearing a long coat?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.83,0:05:37.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person will probably appear again tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.37,0:05:38.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been seeing him at the station a lot lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.07,0:05:39.69,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I've been seeing him at the station a lot lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.42,0:05:43.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please give us a call if you see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.38,0:05:45.30,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Sure, I'll do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.63,0:05:47.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.93,0:05:51.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was, there was.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.43,0:05:56.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A man with a crew-cut came here yesterday around noon asking to borrow the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.14,0:06:01.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently, his cell phone's battery died and he didn't have any change on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.40,0:06:03.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he came here to borrow the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.23,0:06:05.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What, a loud noise?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.98,0:06:06.53,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.99,0:06:09.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A noise so loud that he was forced to hang up the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.65,0:06:11.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was there a noise like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.24,0:06:12.39,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh, that noise must be the nearby construction work.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.39,0:06:14.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that noise must be the nearby construction work.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.16,0:06:18.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Construction work started about a week ago in front of the bank across the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.37,0:06:21.17,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}See, here's that noise again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.63,0:06:26.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The noise is constantly off and on from noon onwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.59,0:06:28.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Construction noise, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.18,0:06:32.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yesterday evening...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.39,0:06:36.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's probably one of our regular customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.68,0:06:40.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A male customer who's always wearing sunglasses and doesn't talk much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.69,0:06:44.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He happened to forget his cell phone, and needed to use the pay phone in our restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.11,0:06:48.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had to make change for him, so I remember it well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.49,0:06:50.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A loud noise?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.03,0:06:52.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.20,0:06:55.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you hear a noise that was so loud it could've prevented the conversation from continuing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.28,0:07:00.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not sure, this street is famous for its serenity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.58,0:07:02.67,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\an8\be10}Good afternoon, residents of this city.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.08,0:07:10.17,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\an8\be10}I am Baishou Shuuhei—please give me your support and you vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.22,0:07:12.47,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\an8\be10}Together, let's transform this city into a quiet neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.13,0:07:14.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.47,0:07:17.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That loud noise persists throughout the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.43,0:07:20.27,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It seems we're right on that campaign car's course.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.27,0:07:21.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A campaign car, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.23,0:07:23.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When will that regular customer come again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.01,0:07:25.15,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}When will that regular customer come again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.15,0:07:27.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He comes everyday.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.11,0:07:29.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he shows up again, I'll give you guys a call.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.23,0:07:29.98,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.36,0:07:31.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I will await your call.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.07,0:07:35.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Each of those three are suspicious, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.66,0:07:38.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All three phone calls meet all the requirements, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.96,0:07:40.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.41,0:07:42.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah-le-le!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.96,0:07:44.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.71,0:07:47.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This cell phone is so strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.46,0:07:49.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle, look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.67,0:07:50.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brat...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.63,0:07:53.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you broke that cell phone or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.38,0:07:54.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.72,0:08:00.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most of the four numbers in the beginning of these phone numbers are similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.44,0:08:06.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,1028...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.36,0:08:08.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,1025...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.98,0:08:12.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These numbers are indeed near each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.57,0:08:15.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're probably neighbors.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.70,0:08:16.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.70,0:08:21.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you before that 10-digit phone numbers beginning with the number 1 don't exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.20,0:08:26.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This has got to be because the chubby owner of this cell phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.37,0:08:31.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Assigned ascending numbers to each person he met during his work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.25,0:08:35.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, which one is the smallest number?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.09,0:08:39.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It should be this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.26,0:08:44.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's over 1000, so he must've known a lot of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.10,0:08:45.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.10,0:08:51.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He might be a door-to-door salesman, and probably just assigned all of these numbers to his clients.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.15,0:08:53.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what's the meaning behind these four numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.07,0:08:56.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this, what does this black dot represent?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.07,0:08:59.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some have black dots and some don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.49,0:09:06.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably marked potential customers when he went to visit them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.71,0:09:15.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The numbers at the end like 150 and 600 most likely represent the quantity of goods he sold...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.13,0:09:16.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't this too strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.76,0:09:22.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, the first four numbers at the beginning are never less than 1022.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.68,0:09:27.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you look closely, two people have the numbers 1031.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.48,0:09:29.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.06,0:09:30.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.48,0:09:32.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.97,0:09:34.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.19,0:09:39.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If there's 1101, then why isn't there any number from 1032 to 1100?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.28,0:09:43.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's in numerical order...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.74,0:09:47.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why does it jump from 1031 to 1101?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.46,0:09:49.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm, could it be this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.88,0:09:52.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be a calendar, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.46,0:09:54.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Calendar?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.75,0:09:58.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,1031 is October 31st.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.01,0:10:01.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,1101 is November 1st or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.55,0:10:02.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.18,0:10:05.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thinking about it that way makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.14,0:10:05.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.56,0:10:12.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If these numbers represent the end of October to the beginning of November of last year...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.77,0:10:14.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That period of time was during the Tohto Diet elections!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.91,0:10:15.51,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.78,0:10:16.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.82,0:10:19.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The neighborhood association's baseball tournament...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.86,0:10:23.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And preparations for the Autumn Festival were also during that time, so it was a busy time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.20,0:10:26.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we can be sure that this man wasn't a resident of this neighborhood, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.41,0:10:29.20,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hey, what's with that tangent?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.37,0:10:31.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.68,0:10:32.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.70,0:10:35.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the four numbers at the beginning represent dates...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.96,0:10:39.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the numbers behind them might be the time he went to visit his clients.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.30,0:10:44.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,150 is 1:50, and 600 is exactly 6:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.47,0:10:47.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why are the surnames in kanji and the given names in katakana?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.47,0:10:51.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because the surname can be found on the home's nameplate...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.85,0:10:56.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whereas the given names can only be discovered while talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.07,0:11:03.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person is probably one of the clients who was angered by the products this cell phone owner sold.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.08,0:11:04.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.12,0:11:09.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person who called from a blocked number and yelled, "Give that guy the phone."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.29,0:11:13.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That same one that also called the phone company and asked for this person's name and address.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.96,0:11:15.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That dangerous person.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.75,0:11:22.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once we know who that person is and where they are, we can ask them for the number to this cell phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.97,0:11:26.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And learn the chubby man's identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.14,0:11:33.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it, if only that guy were still alive, this wouldn't have been so much of a headache.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.14,0:11:33.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.06,0:11:35.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that how it really is?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.77,0:11:38.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's suspicious, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.82,0:11:41.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The place where the cell phone was dropped.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.57,0:11:45.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The antenna of the cell phone was sticking out while the cell phone was nicely folded and placed under the sofa.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.37,0:11:48.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right, that is strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.28,0:11:51.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's as if they wanted someone to find it when they heard the cell phone ringing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.79,0:11:55.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regarding the ring tone, the second phone call from that dangerous person said...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.33,0:11:58.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Did you hear anything ring just now?"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.71,0:12:03.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that chubby man specifically asked the dangerous man to call the phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.22,0:12:08.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to secretly give the cell phone over to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.51,0:12:09.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.76,0:12:13.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that were the case, why didn't he just meet up with the dangerous man here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.06,0:12:20.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If dropped, it would be discovered by an employee, and then he'd have no way of secretly giving it to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.61,0:12:23.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.36,0:12:23.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.24,0:12:27.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he had wanted to give the phone to someone in secret, he wouldn't have deliberately made an effort to retrieve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.70,0:12:31.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not like he mixed up the location or anything, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.54,0:12:33.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mixed up?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.29,0:12:36.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mix things up all the time, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.75,0:12:41.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, at the convenience store, that chubby man...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.00,0:12:42.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.30,0:12:44.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was asking for directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.30,0:12:48.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he's not familiar with this area, he could easily mistake one place for another.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.76,0:12:50.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the suspicious place is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.97,0:12:53.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apollo!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.18,0:12:58.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it the sports shop that has a name similar to our Poirot restaurant?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.44,0:12:59.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.81,0:13:01.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Azusa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.61,0:13:06.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how similar the names are, it's hard to mistake a sports shop for a restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.24,0:13:08.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.24,0:13:09.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Azusa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.78,0:13:13.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is this shop called Poirot?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.87,0:13:18.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've heard of Hercule Poirot from the detective stories, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.75,0:13:21.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our shop owner loves mystery novels, so he got it from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.42,0:13:24.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, you know Poirot, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.71,0:13:26.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's that slightly plump man...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.84,0:13:28.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've seen him on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.93,0:13:31.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He often remarks, "You know, my wife says..."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.51,0:13:33.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police detective who wears a wrinkled coat, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.06,0:13:35.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.77,0:13:38.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy isn't Poirot, he's Columbo.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.65,0:13:44.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could he have mistaken the mystery novels' protagonists?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.98,0:13:48.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, that Columbo restaurant and ours are both in the 5th district.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.49,0:13:54.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that chubby customer only remembered it was a shop in Beika's 5th District named after a detective series...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.20,0:13:55.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be an easy mistake to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.70,0:13:57.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.75,0:13:59.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where to?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.76,0:14:00.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.25,0:14:03.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other famous detective's shop...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.84,0:14:04.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.75,0:14:06.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, I'm going too!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.88,0:14:07.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.17,0:14:09.84,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The identity of that chubby man...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.38,0:14:11.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Will soon be revealed!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.94,0:14:23.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The customer that often wears sunglasses that I mentioned earlier hasn't arrived yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.69,0:14:24.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.86,0:14:27.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, do you mind if we wait here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.44,0:14:27.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.53,0:14:30.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you going to be all right, Azusa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.57,0:14:32.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You just rushed out of the shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.07,0:14:34.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, since the shop owner is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.24,0:14:35.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just need to return by evening when it gets busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.37,0:14:38.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't be able to concentrate while thinking about this anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.37,0:14:39.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Mister...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.41,0:14:43.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did that customer ever ask you anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.84,0:14:46.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whenever he comes, he always asks...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.42,0:14:49.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I've come across a lost cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.09,0:14:52.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.14,0:14:55.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like this is the right place.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.30,0:14:55.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.31,0:14:59.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, he's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.73,0:15:01.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.85,0:15:02.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.44,0:15:06.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But is something the matter with that customer?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.65,0:15:08.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.61,0:15:11.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to talk to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.82,0:15:16.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll know if he's the person who called after hearing his voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.20,0:15:18.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I should go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.20,0:15:21.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is when you let a man handle things.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.46,0:15:27.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.55,0:15:29.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.17,0:15:31.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you going to talk to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.55,0:15:33.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before we talk to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.01,0:15:36.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should hear my deductions.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.85,0:15:41.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, the strange names written in katakana in this cell phone's contact list.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.73,0:15:47.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although they look like names of people, they're actually abbreviated names of certain organizations.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.73,0:15:48.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Certain organizations?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.28,0:15:50.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please let me see that for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.19,0:15:52.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.82,0:15:58.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this cell phone's contact list, there are many strange names that don't seem like family names, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.29,0:16:03.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you mean "Kenbashi Shou"{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and "Daitoma Cho"{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.12,0:16:03.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.58,0:16:07.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they're the names of places, I've heard of them, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.08,0:16:09.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've never heard of anyone with surnames like those.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.93,0:16:10.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.71,0:16:14.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those names likely belong to organizations based in those areas.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.68,0:16:17.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For example, "Kenbashi Shou" represents the Kenbashi Shopping District...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.30,0:16:19.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And "Daitoma Cho" represents the Daitoma Neighborhood Association.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.60,0:16:23.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we read it that way, it all makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.14,0:16:25.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Aida Ken" is Aida Construction.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.56,0:16:28.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Ishizawa Seisaku" is Ishizawa Manufacturing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.77,0:16:33.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, there are 10-digit numbers recorded along with each of those names.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.28,0:16:36.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first four digits represent dates.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.16,0:16:38.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The numbers after represent the amount of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.07,0:16:40.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The black dots beside the names represent "black figures".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.12,0:16:42.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In short, revenue.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.41,0:16:46.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those without black dots are the opposite: Expenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.87,0:16:51.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Taking into account the dates were concentrated around the time of last year's election...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.67,0:16:52.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's only one conclusion that can be drawn!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.96,0:16:53.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.51,0:16:56.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're secret campaign financing records?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.84,0:16:58.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.18,0:17:03.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though we don't know how that chubby man came into the possession of these records...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.39,0:17:08.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fact remains that he had intended to use this to blackmail someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.15,0:17:12.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason he entered the records into the cell phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.57,0:17:17.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was in order to show the other party proof that he indeed possessed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.07,0:17:19.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, that person is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.24,0:17:23.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's probably someone hired by the one whose campaign car is making the rounds on the streets in this area...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.37,0:17:25.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Diet Member Baishou.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.00,0:17:29.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All for the purpose of getting the secret records back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.04,0:17:33.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason he suddenly hung up while on the phone with the telephone company...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.38,0:17:37.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was because he heard the sounds from Diet Member Baishou's campaign van.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.59,0:17:41.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While searching for the guy with the secret records...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.76,0:17:44.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He thought it would have been bad if it was found out that he was connected with Diet Member Baishou.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.97,0:17:46.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so he instantly hung up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.81,0:17:50.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, the man with the sunglasses was the one who chose this restaurant as the location for the transaction...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.44,0:17:52.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he was a regular customer here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.86,0:17:58.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had originally planned to call the cell phone from here and take it without anyone noticing...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.61,0:18:01.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the chubby man mixed up the location.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.07,0:18:08.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why didn't that chubby man contact us once he realized that he was at the wrong restaurant?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.75,0:18:11.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's probably because, by the time he realized that...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.50,0:18:15.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was already past the time they'd arranged to do the exchange.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.05,0:18:19.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The original plan was to have the shop owner find the phone after it started ringing...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.76,0:18:24.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then have the man in sunglasses claim it was his.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.26,0:18:29.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though he mistook the place, he could easily get it back at Poirot by calling his cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.64,0:18:34.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, if he did that, there was a chance the man in sunglasses could've picked up and ascertained his voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.90,0:18:41.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That chubby man had probably used fax and text messages to communicate regarding the transaction...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.78,0:18:46.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to prevent his face or voice from being noticed and exposing his identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.83,0:18:52.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's also why he had the line killed and removed the production sticker from the cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.42,0:18:58.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the reason that chubby man rushed back to Poirot was...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.01,0:19:02.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was to make sure whether or not the man in sunglasses had taken the phone or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.39,0:19:08.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it had been handed over to the police as a lost item, his plan to get money would have been destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.18,0:19:11.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if that's the case...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.02,0:19:15.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then no matter how much we question that man in sunglasses, he won't say anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.73,0:19:17.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, there's still a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.48,0:19:19.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.57,0:19:23.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Azusa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.78,0:19:24.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.66,0:19:26.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.91,0:19:32.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Miss, I wonder who lost that cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.29,0:19:34.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If no one wants it, can you give it to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.13,0:19:38.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is my first time seeing a cell phone with such a strange case.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.75,0:19:39.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah-le-le!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.88,0:19:42.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are so many strange names and numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.47,0:19:43.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.68,0:19:44.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, brat!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.35,0:19:47.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mean, little boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.47,0:19:51.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's actually my cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.06,0:19:53.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.31,0:19:54.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Show me some proof, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.10,0:19:56.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.44,0:19:57.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.19,0:20:00.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If this really does belong to you, you should know the number of this cell phone, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.24,0:20:04.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can test to see if the number goes through...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.66,0:20:06.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So tell me the number.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.54,0:20:08.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just hurry up and give me the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.83,0:20:10.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a police woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.75,0:20:14.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe I should give it to her...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.12,0:20:15.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.75,0:20:17.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.21,0:20:19.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you the number.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.09,0:20:24.38,Narration,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And so, we finally obtained the chubby man's phone number.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.18,0:20:28.64,Narration,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Using that number, the police managed to locate his apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.89,0:20:32.64,Narration,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It seems that man was likely an investigative reporter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.73,0:20:37.69,Narration,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Buried under heaps of receipts, a copy of the secret records was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.11,0:20:42.36,Narration,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And on it, the names, dates, and the\Namounts of money were clearly written.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.94,0:20:45.07,Narration,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It was more than enough evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.20,0:20:49.37,Narration,,0,0,0,,{\be10}As such, in the middle of his campaign, Diet Member Baishou...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.37,0:20:53.29,Narration,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And those who received money from him, were all arrested one after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.79,0:22:22.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.46,0:22:25.09,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I am Mouri Kogoro.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.50,0:22:27.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cup of hot coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.51,0:22:31.38,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I am but a humble detective engaged in the battle against the shadow of society known as crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.14,0:22:34.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No, allow me to correct that...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.80,0:22:36.27,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I am Mouri Kogoro...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.27,0:22:38.10,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A {\i1}famous{\i0} detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.60,0:22:39.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.44,0:22:42.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much for yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.36,0:22:46.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If anything else comes up, feel free to come to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.48,0:22:46.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.69,0:22:48.74,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.74,0:22:50.52,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's no case I cannot solve.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.52,0:22:51.99,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}For example, that student...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.57,0:22:58.41,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}After successfully getting into college, he has no need to come here to study anymore, yet he still comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.70,0:23:01.08,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's no doubt that he has a crush...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.79,0:23:03.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A case!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.16,0:23:07.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, this is famous detective—
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.80,0:23:09.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.26,0:23:09.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.05,0:23:11.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.09,0:23:15.51,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It looks like today's club activities are going to run a bit late, so could you do some shopping for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.06,0:23:18.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.68,0:23:20.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see... potatoes...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.25,0:23:20.82,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Let's see... potatoes...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.82,0:23:21.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Potatoes...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.14,0:23:25.38,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Carrots... onions... pork... and apples.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.39,0:23:27.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that we're eating curry tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.90,0:23:29.94,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Could it be that we're eating curry tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.36,0:23:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's correct!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.45,0:23:32.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As expected of a famous detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.16,0:23:34.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.53,0:23:35.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a big case.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.62,0:23:37.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll get to the scene right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.74,0:23:38.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,HOT!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.54,0:23:39.62,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Dad, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.41,0:23:42.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Coffee... coffee... hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.83,0:23:45.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Nothing to do as usual, right, Uncle?
